Author: Jake Reed [aut, cre] (<https://orcid.org/0000-0002-8384-3593>)
Maintainer: Jake Reed <hreed.ga@gmail.com>
Description: Wrapper for 'Minimap2'. 'Minimap2' is a very valuable long read aligner for the Pacbio and Oxford Nanopore Technologies sequencing platforms. minimapR is an R wrapper for 'minimap2' which was developed by Heng Li <me@liheng.org>. 
Li, Heng (2018) <doi: https://doi.org/10.1093/bioinformatics/bty191> "Minimap2: pairwise alignment for nucleotide sequences".
	*SPECIAL NOTE Examples can only be run from 'GitHub' installation.
	*SPECIAL NOTE If using a Windows operating system, installation of the 'MSYS2' Linux emulator is required.
    *SPECIAL NOTE If using a Mac operating system, installation of 'Homebrew' is required.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Depends: Rsamtools, git2r, pafr 
